rComments: MUCH improved over cs431. More compact slides, pays more attention to students. nicely done!

Excited to take the class until the 2nd/3rd lecture. Marco spent his time (back turned) reading the 50-70 powerpoint slides for the day. Slides were full of C-code and material copy/pasted from the man pages that were quickly clicked through because of its simplicity. I think he was competent but just couldn't express himself. Would not recommend.
Well intentioned, but has no idea how to teach. Putting C code on a slide or referencing the man pages every 2 minutes is not teaching.

Marco definitely knows his stuff , but that translates to about 50 slides/lecture of material. This is extremely hard to study. Marco means well, but it seems he is more of a researcher rather than a lecturer.
